body:
First line in main function compiles with error, but second and third compiles without error.

```rust
#![allow(unused)]
#![feature(decl_macro)]
#![feature(try_blocks)]
#![feature(type_ascription)]

pub macro test_macro {
    () => {
        try {
            let mut exit_code = 0;
            if exit_code < 0 {
                Err(exit_code)?;
            }
            exit_code
        }: Result<usize, usize>
    }
}

fn main() {
    test_macro!(); // Err
    // test_macro!().unwrap(); // Ok
    // let t = test_macro!(); // Ok
}
```

([Playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?gist=c3b207c6c51d424c217b51c97ce02ca8&version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018))

Errors:

```
   Compiling playground v0.0.1 (/playground)
error: expected expression, found `:`
  --> src/main.rs:14:10
   |
14 |         }: Result<usize, usize>
   |          ^ expected expression
...
19 |     test_macro!(); // Err
   |     -------------- in this macro invocation

